Because we can not just delete log[prev_log_id.index..], (which results in loss of committed entry), the commit index must be updated only after append-entries and must point to a log entry that is consistent to the leader. Or there would be chance applying an uncommitted entry on a follower: R0 1,1 1,2 3,3
R1 1,1 1,2 2,3
R2 1,1 1,2 3,3 R0 to R1 append_entries: entries=[{1,2}], prev_log_id = {1,1}, commit_index = 3 R1 accepted this append-entries request but was not aware of that entry {2,3} is inconsistent to leader. Then it will update commit_index to 3 and apply {2,3}

