A request is some data that modifies the raft state machine. A response is some data that the raft state machine returns to client. Request and response can be any types that impl AppData and AppDataResponse, e.g.: #[derive(Clone, Debug, Serialize, Deserialize)]
pub struct ClientRequest {/* fields */}
impl AppData for ClientRequest {} #[derive(Clone, Debug, Serialize, Deserialize)]
pub struct ClientResponse(Result<Option<String>, ClientError>);
impl AppDataResponse for ClientResponse {} These two types are totally application specific, and are mainly related to the state machine implementation in RaftStorage.

